EUNICE on Skeem Saam is having a really tough time. Nothing in her life is adding up, and getting help also seems difficult. While she’s trying to find another job following her dismissal at Cafe Rovuwa, she is having second thoughts. Things are not as easy as she thought they would be. Job hunting has left a massive emotional scar and is taxing her financially. Her storyline is showcasing what a lot of young people in Mzansi are going through. They have qualifications, yet the job market does not have enough openings. ALSO READ | DJ SBU UVUSA ABALELE She cannot even afford to make copies of the required documents to apply for a job. We can only hope that a silver lining will soon appear. Meanwhile ziyakhala on Gomora. Gladys has learnt about Melusi and Thathi’s moment of passion. She threatened to divorce Melusi, but he doesn’t care. This is because although his marriage is hanging by a thread, he is stressing over Thathi, who is about to get married. He has even decided to risk it all to make Thathi change her mind, but will she budge and fall for him? Things are getting worse for Lwandle on The Estate. Her memory loss challenge is worsening but her family refuses to get her the necessary help. They’re forcing her to remain silent about the accident as it may lead to her and her accomplice going to jail. For how long will she keep her silence for?